'''Christina Novelli''', born {{Birth date and age|1985|11|27|df=yes}}, is a [[England|British]] [[DJ]] and [[vocalist]]  who resides in [[London]].  She is the daughter of [[Jean-Christophe Novelli]], a [[France|French]] celebrity chef.<ref>channel5.com: [http://www.channel5.com/shows/candy-bar-girls/cast/christina-novelli Channel 5 Candy Bar Girls]</ref>

== Early career ==

At the age of 17, influenced by the music of [[Motown]], [[Johnny Cash]], [[Elvis]], [[Tina Turner]], [[Lauryn Hill]],<ref>reverbnation.com: [http://www.reverbnation.com/christinanovelli/ About Christina Novelli]</ref><ref>http://www.oceanradiochilled.com: [http://www.oceanradiochilled.com/#!THE-BEAUTIFUL-VOICES--BEGINNING-OF-A-SERIES--CHRISTINA-NOVELLI/c1gsj/EB83C665-2C59-48DE-AAAF-3FA71586E1BF/ THE BEAUTIFUL VOICES : BEGINNING OF A SERIES : CHRISTINA NOVELLI]</ref> Novelli started fronting her own bands.<ref>gaystarnews.com: [http://www.gaystarnews.com/article/bisexual-singer-christina-novelli-her-love-affair-music-and-cooking130812/ Bisexual singer Christina Novelli on her love affair with music and cooking]</ref> In 2011 Novelli starred in a reality TV show on [[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5]] called Candy Bar Girls, a documentary series revealing the lives and loves of the staff and regulars at the world-famous Candy Bar in [[Soho]], [[London]].<ref>channel5.com: [http://www.channel5.com/shows/candy-bar-girls/ Real lesbians. Real lives. No cliches]</ref> While on the show, Novelli could be seen performing a mix of some of her own material along with many covers, making them her own. Some of the songs she sang were [[Goo Goo Dolls]]', <U+2018>Iris<U+2019>, [[Damien Rice]]<U+2019>s <U+2018>Cannonball<U+2019> and [[Bruno Mars]]<U+2019> <U+2018>Just the way you are.'<ref>altsounds.com: [http://hangout.altsounds.com/reviews/136312-christina-novelli-candy-bar-london-live.html Christina Novelli at the Candy Bar, London &#91;Live&#93;]</ref>

== Breakthrough 2012-2013 ==

In early 2012, Novelli collaborated with EDM producer and DJ [[Gareth Emery]], on the track 'Concrete Angel'. By June of the same year, 'Concrete Angel' had entered the [[Billboard (magazine)]] at #15 on the 'Dance Music' charts, and currently has over 20 million views on [[YouTube]].<ref>fandalism.com: [http://fandalism.com/bencollier/ Ben Collier Pianist in London, United Kingdom]</ref><ref>YouTube: [http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0dFz10R529g/ Gareth Emery - Concrete Angel]</ref> Since then, Novelli has also collaborated with the likes of [[Dash Berlin]] and [[Armin Van Buuren]]. In December 2013, "Satellite" by Justin Caruso & [[Dave Aud<U+00E9>]] featuring Christina Novelli, debuted as the #47 Dance Club Song in [[Billboard (magazine)]].<ref>billboard.com: [http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/5855090/chart-highlights-robin-thicke-bastille-end-year-with-new-no-1s/ Chart Highlights]</ref>

== DJ career from 2013 to present ==

In 2013 Novelli began DJing all over the world including iconic venues LIV Miami, [[Pacha]] NYC, and [[Ultra Music Festival]]. Her DJ style is house music, but she also plays hip-hop, trap, hard style, and trance. Novelli launched a radio show called #TITS in March 2014, the acronym stands for 'This Is The Sound'. She is set to release her debut solo record in 2014..{{Citation needed|date=November 2014}}

== Awards and nominations ==

Christina Novelli and [[Gareth Emery]]'s song 'Concrete Angel' was nominated for the 28th Annual [[International Dance Music Awards]] for 'Best Trance Track' of 2013.<ref>IDMA Nomination: [http://wintermusicconference.com/events/idmas/index.php?wmcyear=2013/ Winter Music Conference 2014]</ref>

